      "name": "Egyptian Chariot",
      "desc": "Light, fast, and built for archery. Two horses, a driver, and a bowman standing on a platform of bent wood and leather. The pharaoh's chariot corps was the first mobile striking force in history \u2014 they didn't charge into infantry, they circled and shot until the enemy broke.",
