      "name": "Trireme",
      "desc": "A hundred and seventy oars in three banks, a bronze ram at the waterline, and the most manoeuvrable warship of the ancient world. The trireme fights by ramming \u2014 she accelerates to combat speed, strikes the enemy hull at the waterline, backs away, and watches her opponent sink.",
      "notes": "The ram is the primary weapon. Ramming uses standard vehicle collision rules, but the bronze ram adds AP. The tactical game is positioning \u2014 hit the enemy amidships while presenting only your reinforced bow. Boarding is a backup plan for when the ram misses. Run ancient naval battles as positioning contests.",
